commit_message:
(WIP) Use multiprocessing in UserGenerator for creating users

This commit is actually not working - we have RuntimeError while running a test task.
I need a review and comments about the idea of this commit and what is wrong.

The error is:
RuntimeError: maximum recursion depth exceeded while calling a Python object

The task is:
{
    "KeystoneBasic.create_delete_user": [
	{
	    "args": {"name_length": 10},
            "execution": "continuous",
	    "config": {
		"times": 100,
		"active_users": 10,
		"tenants": 5,
		"users_per_tenant": 10
	    }
	}
    ]
}

Blueprint conrurrent-creation-of-users

Change-Id: I30ea35ec4310035b3e100160ac63c814a86398f6

